At least five people have been killed and over 300 properties damaged or completely gutted since the fires broke out on Tuesday. CAPE TOWN – The Knynsa council has declared the region a disaster area following the devastating fires that tore through the town. At least five people have been killed and over 300 properties damaged or completely gutted since the fires broke out on Tuesday. Unfavorable weather has caused concern of possible flare-ups. Municipal spokesperson Fran Kirsten says local firefighting crews, including the defence force, will remain on the ground until at least the end of the weekend to monitor the situation.  “Following an urgent council meeting this afternoon, the Knysna municipality has declared Greater Knysna a disaster area following the fires. This adds to the Knysna being declared a water disaster area as well.” 